File: Samwu says some municipalities haven’t distributed personal protective equipment. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Municipal Workers’ Union (Samwu) says municipalities aren’t ready for Level 3 on Monday, especially those in hotspots. It’s asked members to refuse to work if their health and safety can’t be guaranteed. Samwu says some municipalities haven’t distributed personal protective equipment. READ: Samwu won't take part in 'salary cut challenge' They claim there is no budget and no help has come from national government. Other municipalities have asked staff to buy their own. Samwu says the failure to provide the correct safety equipment has led to almost 200 municipal worker infections and two deaths. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.